Overview of OSSEC architecture and configs

OSSEC can run either in agent or agentless mode based on the device and the compliance. Some network devices like firewalls and routers do not have the option to install packages. The agentless setup will be the ideal and the ultimate solution in that case. 

Heads up: In this demo, we will utilize the agent installation, which consists of an agent (OSSEC agent) and a server (OSSEC manager). 

OSSEC files are all located under /var/ossec. In that directory, our focus will be on the following:

  • etc: OSSEC-related config files
  • rules: OOB (Out Of The Box) rules provided by OSSEC

Figure 1 - zoom in

OSSEC main config file path is /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf. Within this file, you can enable or disable rules and also define the alerting for those rules.

Figure 2 - zoom in

As you can see from the above screenshot, the config file has multiple sections, such as <global>, <rules>, and <syscheck>. We will edit one section in the upcoming demo to fine-tune a pre-existing rule. Bear with me.
